.V= $Header: abs.3 1.5 86/05/13 $
.TH ABS 3 "\*(V)" "7th Edition"
.SH NAME
abs \- integer absolute value
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B abs(i)
.B int i;
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Abs
returns the absolute value of its integer operand.
.SH SEE ALSO
floor(3M) for
.I fabs
.SH BUGS
Applying the \f2abs\fP function to the most negative integer generates a
result which is the most negative integer.  That is, 
.IP "abs(0x80000000)"
.LP
returns 0x80000000 as a result.
